The paper discusses the problem of one-way functions, which is a fundamental concept in cryptography and computer science. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper deals with combinatorial aspects of one-way functions, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses subtleties in basic definitions, which could make it relevant to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
